Know your nut/seed butters! ü•ú‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
High quality nut/seed butters are super tasty, nutritious, and make for an easy addition to meals, so I outlined some of the key benefits of four different kinds for you.üòäReminder though to always check the ingredient label of your nut butter because some brands like to add oils, sugar or even high fructose corn syrup. I always try to opt for nut butters that contain just the nut on the ingredient label or nuts & salt.‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
Sunflower butter- Sunflower butter is especially high in vitamin E and selenium. It is also the most allergy-friendly out of the bunch since it‚Äôs a seed butter, not a nut. Sunflower butter is also packed with antioxidants including phenolic acids and flavonoids as well as magnesium, protein,¬† and linoleic fatty acids that may help lower blood pressure, cholesterol and blood sugar. .‚†Ä
Cashew butter - While it‚Äôs very low in fiber, it has lots of beneficial vitamins and minerals like vitamins E, K, and B-6, potassium, and folate. Cashews also have very high levels of lutein and zeaxanthin, which are antioxidants known to help protect the eyes.üëÄ‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
Peanut Butter- Peanut butter has the highest amount of protein of the nut butters and even more so if you opt for chunky. üòãAlthough it contains the word ‚Äúnut‚Äù, it is technically a legume not a nut. It also has high amounts of monounsaturated fat, which has been linked to a reduction in heart disease and better blood sugar control. Peanut butter also contains vitamins and minerals like vitamin E, calcium, iron, potassium, biotin, magnesium, and zinc. PB also contains more B vitamins than almonds.‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
Almond Butter- Almond butter has more minerals than peanut butter, with the exception of selenium. It also has the highest amount of fiber of the four and contains nearly 3X as much vitamin E, 7X more calcium, and 2X the amount of iron that peanut butter has. Almond butter is also packed with minerals like potassium, zinc, biotin, and magnesium and is high in monounsaturated fat, which has been linked to improved blood sugar control.‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
All of these nut butters are delicious and nutritious for different reasons!üòÅ‚†Ä
.‚†Ä

Upgraded 6 Ingredient Eggnog & 3 Ingredient Hot Chocolate! üç´‚òïÔ∏è(Swipe ‚ñ∂Ô∏è to see ingredients laid out) ‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
While of course enjoying the standard versions of these holiday drinks as a treat is totally fine, I thought I‚Äôd share these two upgraded recipes so that you can enjoy a cup of hot chocolate or eggnog more regularly and from your own home. Both of these drinks have been one of my most requested recipes üòã‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
Here‚Äôs what you need for the eggnog:‚†Ä
8-12oz unsweetened almond milk ‚†Ä
2 egg yolks‚†Ä
1 tbsp maple syrup‚†Ä
¬º tsp vanilla extract ‚†Ä
¬º tsp nutmeg ‚†Ä
Cinnamon to taste ‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
What to do:‚†Ä
1- Beat the egg yolks, maple syrup, and almond milk in a separate bowl‚†Ä
2- Heat the mixture on the stove over medium heat and whisk regularly until it reaches 160¬∞‚†Ä (the temperature that is safe to eat eggs at). It shouldn‚Äôt boil. If it boils, remove to an empty burner and keep mixing.‚†Ä
3- Once it reaches 160¬∞, pour into a blender. ‚†Ä
4- Add the vanilla extract and spices. ‚†Ä
4- Blend and sip! ‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
Here‚Äôs what you need for the hot chocolate:‚†Ä
8-12oz unsweetened almond milk‚†Ä
2 tbsp chocolate protein powder (I prefer the taste of plant based protein in this recipe but whey should work fine too)‚†Ä
1 tbsp chocolate chips ‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
What to do:‚†Ä
1- Heat the almond milk on the stove. ‚†Ä
2- Add the hot almond milk and rest of ingredients to a blender.‚†Ä
3- Blend and enjoy! ‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
It‚Äôs that easy! Hope you enjoy üòò‚†Ä
.‚†Ä

10 ways to be happier! üòÑ Its perfectly healthy to let yourself feel a range of emotions. However, if you‚Äôre feeling down, more often than not, here are some practical steps to brighten your mood.‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
1 - Start a daily gratitude practice: Writing down a few reasons you‚Äôre grateful can make a huge difference in mood (like I do w/ @fiveminutejournal). This study confirmed the positive effects on counting blessings vs. burdens on your mood (1)‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
2 - Get some sun: Vitamin D deficiency is tied to depression, so try to get¬†¬†10-20 min exposure/day.‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
3 - Make time for exercise: Exercise releases endorphins, the mood-boosting chemical. This 2012 study also showed that long-term physical activity was linked to lasting happiness (2)‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
4 - Get more sleep or nap: In a study, subjects who slept 4 hrs/night showed declining levels of optimism & sociability as a function of days of inadequate sleep (3)‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
5 - Meditate more: Many studies have shown the positive effects of meditation on brain health & reducing anxiety/depression symptoms. This 2015 study showed meditation to improve sleep quality, leading to improved mood (4)‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
6 - Treat yourself to flowers: This study showed the group gifted flowers had a more positive emotional improvement than the group gifted candles (5)‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
7 - Smile more often: This study showed that participants who smiled during a stressful activity had lower heart rate levels after the activity than those who didn‚Äôt. (6) In a way, it seems that smiling tricks the brain & body into a calming response.‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
8 - Eat more fruits & veggies: Studies show solid evidence that a diet rich in veggies and fruit is associated w/ greater happiness & positive well being (7)‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
9 - Spend quality time with positive ppl: The happiest participants spent 25% less time alone, 70% more time talking, & 2X as many deep convos. The study demonstrated happy life is social rather than solitary (8)‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
10 - Plan a trip: This study showed people tend to be happier in anticipation of an experiential purchase rather than material goods (9) .‚†Ä
Note if you‚Äôre suffering with clinical depression, there is no substitute for professional help ‚ù§Ô∏è‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
#happiness #health

The less is more approach with this easy recipe with chicken kebabs ‚ù§Ô∏è A simple yet delicious meal for dinner.‚†Ä
‚Äî‚†Ä
Love this recipe by my friend, @livevitae ! (Checkout his recipe page). Full instructions below:‚†Ä
‚Äî‚†Ä
I opted for chicken thighs as they are tastier and do not dry out like breast.‚†Ä
Feel free to add eggplant or zucchini to the kebab party üéâ. I used guacamole as a side but feel free to adjust to your needs like adding a side of sweet potato or rice!‚†Ä
‚Äî‚†Ä
Serves 1 but easily x2 x4 x8‚†Ä
Calories 545 : P 40 C 31 F 29‚†Ä
Ingredients:‚†Ä
125grams chicken thighs skinless‚†Ä
1/2 red yellow green bell peppers‚†Ä
1/2 tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil‚†Ä
1 avocado‚†Ä
1/2 red onion‚†Ä
Handful cherry tomatoes‚†Ä
Spice mix of : cumin + coriander + smoked paprika‚†Ä
‚Äî‚†Ä
Recipe:‚†Ä
1. Dice the chicken thighs into halves. We are aiming for 2 inch pieces so everything is equal. Mix the chicken thighs with the spices.‚†Ä
2. Dice the peppers the same size.‚†Ä
3. Next alternatively add them to a skewer.‚†Ä
4. Preheat Cast iron paddle or bbq to medium and cook 3 minutes per side.‚†Ä
5. Once lightly browned all over, transfer to oven and cook for 5 mins to cook through.‚†Ä
6. While in oven, prepare the guacamole.‚†Ä
Mash an avocado, add the oil, finely diced tomato + red onion.‚†Ä
7. Remove kebab and plate up alongside guacamole.‚†Ä
8. Season to taste with salt, squeeze of lime and üëåüèª‚†Ä
‚Äî‚†Ä
This is a simple recipe. Feel free to use lamb, beef or throw some organ meats like liver on there too!‚†Ä
.‚†Ä

Are you more of matcha fan or green tea drinker? üçµ  Personally, I love both and wanted to talk about the main differences below:‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä
While green tea is made from the steeping of leaves in hot water,  matcha is made from the whole tea leaf ground into a fine powder and thus making it more concentrated. The leaves are also often grown slightly differently. Matcha tea bushes are shielded from the sun for about 20-30 days which increases the chlorophyll levels & production of amino acids.‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä
Since green tea does have less caffeine, green tea could be a better fit for someone who is super sensitive to caffeine.‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä
Something to look out for with matcha, in particular,is whether or not the drink comes pre-sweetened. Matcha in coffee shops or stores can often be sweetened with way too much sugar. I looked up the typical matcha green tea latte from a popular coffee chain and it comes with a whooping serving of 32g sugar - yikes! I suggest asking for your matcha lattes unsweetened and adding your own stevia or honey instead.‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä
Let me know if you have questions below!‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä
Xoxo,‚†Ä‚†Ä
Amanda‚†Ä‚†Ä

Know your oils and their smoking point! üî•‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä
First off, what is a ‚Äúsmoke point‚Äù? The smoke point is the temperature at which an oil starts to undergo what‚Äôs called ‚Äúlipidperoxidation‚Äù and becomes rancid. That‚Äôs why it‚Äôs important to pay attention to an oil‚Äôs smoke point when cooking or baking. It is also a common misconception that you can‚Äôt saut√© with olive oil. You definitely can but it would be best to use it at low to medium heats.‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä
Below is a list of some of the good oils, benefits and heat toleration:‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä
Avocado oil - great for high heats, good source of lutein, increases absorption of carotenoids.‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä
Coconut oil (virgin) - great for low to medium heats, great source of MCTs‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä
Walnut oil - great for low to medium heats, good source of omega-3s‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä
Ghee butter - great for high heats, contains vitamin A, E & K.‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä
Olive oil - great for low to medium heats, rich in polyphenols, great source of monounsaturated fat.‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä
Minimize the use of these oils:‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä
Soybean oil - shown in many studies to be highly inflammatory (due to high omega 6 saturation levels). Over 90% of soy is GMO = more pesticides. .‚†Ä‚†Ä
Canola oil - uses a synthetic chemical extraction methods, bleaching, and deodorizing.‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä
Hydrogenated vegetable oils - high trans fat, inflammatory, impairs endothelial function, increase risk for cardiovascular disease‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä
My personal go-tos are olive oil, avocado, coconut and ghee! What are your favorites? Xoxo,‚†Ä‚†Ä
Amanda.‚†Ä‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä

.‚Å†‚†Ä
I know the holidays can be a chaotic time so I thought I‚Äôd share something simple and delicious you can enjoy with family and friends over the holidays. And I mean who doesn‚Äôt love a chocolate-y combo. Just make sure your husband doesn‚Äôt get his hands on it before you get the party üôäü§£ Full instructions below:‚Å†‚†Ä
.‚Å†‚†Ä
What you need:‚Å†‚†Ä
(Makes 8-10 servings)‚Å†‚†Ä
3-4 85% dark chocolate bars (about 250g or 1-2 bags dark chocolate chips)‚Å†‚†Ä

4 Steps to a Fitmas Tree! üéÑ üí´‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
Looking for something fun and healthy to do over the holidays? I got you covered! Not only is this idea super cute but it‚Äôs very practical.‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
I shared this fruit tree with my friends the other day and it was a total hit! üòã It‚Äôs very easy to grab the fruit off the toothpicks and of course aesthetically pleasing.‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
What you need:‚†Ä
1 pineapple‚†Ä
1 pear‚†Ä
1 wooden shish kebob skewer‚†Ä
Pack of toothpicks‚†Ä
Star cookie cutter (or if you‚Äôre skilled, you can just cut it in a star shape)‚†Ä
Strawberries‚†Ä
Purple grapes‚†Ä
Green grapes‚†Ä
Kiwis‚†Ä
Blackberries‚†Ä
(Option to add other fruits like oranges etc - have fun with it!)‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
What to do:‚†Ä
Step 1 - Slice off the edges of the pineapple & the top. Cut an extra top slice for the star (make sure it‚Äôs thick enough so the star isn‚Äôt flimsy).‚†Ä
Step 2 - Trim the top off a pear and use the shish kebob skewer to connect the pear and pineapple.‚†Ä
Step 3 - Prepare the colorful fruit. Cut the tops off of strawberries and cut kiwis into slices.‚†Ä
Step 4 - Use toothpicks to stick the fruit around the pineapple and pear. Use a toothpick to stick the pineapple star on the very top.‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
I‚Äôd love to see the versions you create! Make sure to tag me in your pics and stories so I can reshare xoxo,‚†Ä

How to create a healthy plate no matter what diet/lifestyle you follow! üå±‚ù§Ô∏è(*Swipe to see 4 more examples*)‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
Shoutout to my friend Tyler aka @functional.foods for creating so many great visuals around healthy eating. He really practices what he preaches. .‚†Ä
Here‚Äôs the deal. Whether you‚Äôre paleo, keto, vegan, gluten free or just follow a general healthy lifestyle, we all benefit from eating more whole foods and a variety of plants. I love these illustrations because it shows how any of these diets could end up on the processed end of the spectrum.  Some things to keep in mind when creating a healthier plate:‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
1Ô∏è‚É£ Lots of vegetables‚†Ä
2Ô∏è‚É£ An abundance of diverse color‚†Ä
3Ô∏è‚É£ Nutrient-density‚†Ä
4Ô∏è‚É£ Most likely either include a starchy carb or healthy fat ‚†Ä
5Ô∏è‚É£ Add some filling protein whether that is animal or plant based‚†Ä
.‚†Ä

One question I get asked a lot is ‚Äúare low calorie diets hurting my metabolism?‚Äù‚†Ä
-‚†Ä
Great post by @thobrandt‚†Ä
-‚†Ä
And while that can be true in some cases, it‚Äôs more the fact that low calorie diets (‚Äúcrash diets‚Äù) lead to binging. And because they‚Äôre so extreme, they often fail due to the unrealistic expectations. Metabolic adaptation is definitely real, but in most cases the reason you‚Äôre not losing weight on a really low calorie diet is because you‚Äôre following an unsustainable plan that leads to binging, not that your metabolism all of a sudden stopped working.‚†Ä
-‚†Ä
So when it comes to weight loss, you have to set yourself up for success by not going into such a big deficit because you are only human. It‚Äôs important to set goals that are attainable & sustainable.‚†Ä
-‚†Ä
So, Here‚Äôs the takeaway üëâ It‚Äôs not necessarily that low calorie diets don‚Äôt work, it‚Äôs that going into too big of a deficit is unsustainable (& also has negative impacts on your health). So it makes much more sense to be in that moderate deficit where u can still enjoy your diet & live an awesome lifestyle while making progress, & have energy in the gym and build/sustain muscle mass. sustainability=progress, always. PLUS why would you want to be miserable?‚†Ä
.‚†Ä‚†Ä

Know your sweeteners! üòã‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
I wanted to give you the lowdown on the different types of sweeteners you can use! There are so many alternatives to table sugar that taste great & make for a more nutritious treat ‚ú®‚†Ä
. ‚†Ä
Coconut sugar- is made from the dehydrated fluid inside of coconut palms. ü•• Compared to table sugar that has no vital nutrients, coconut sugar is packed w/ antioxidants, polyphenols, & minerals like iron, zinc, and potassium. Coconut sugar also contains a fiber called inulin which may slow the absorption of glucose & explains why the glycemic index is 54, rather than table sugar‚Äôs GI of 60.‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
Dates- are awesome because they are sweet like sugar but full of fiber, vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants like flavonoids, carotenoids, & phenolic acid. They are easy to add into recipes & have a GI of 44.‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
Honey- High quality honey is full of important antioxidants including phenolic compounds like flavonoids. Because it is so sweet, you don‚Äôt have to use a lot of it which is an added bonus. While it doesn‚Äôt have fiber or protein, it‚Äôs still a great alternative to table sugar. üçØ Make sure to go for a raw honey though!‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
Monk Fruit-is a green melon native to southern China that got it‚Äôs name from the monks who cultivated it. The extract is similar to Stevia in that it has 0 calories & carbs, & does not raise blood glucose levels. It is 150-250 times sweeter than table sugar, and has mogrosides that are said to be anti-inflammatory.‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
Maple Syrup- Real maple syrup (not maple flavored syrup that can be loaded w/ refined sugar) has a GI of 54. While it can be high in sugar, it has minerals like manganese and zinc and one study even found 24 different antioxidants in it! This would be a great choice if you like the taste of maple & want to add that flavor to your treat. üçÅ‚†Ä
.‚†Ä
Stevia- has 0 calories & is much sweeter than table sugar which means you don‚Äôt need as much. One study even found that switching from refined sugar to stevia significantly lowered insulin & glucose levels in participants; just be cautious to avoid stevia products that are highly processed. .‚†Ä
While all sweeteners should be consumed in moderation, these are more nutritious choices
